Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["README", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"98620dcb-b19f-47ad-8179-76bc3b4a9ae9"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Notations", "Chapter",ExpressionUUID->"384d1439-e438-4ec8-a6d4-574ccbdbc736"],

Cell["Here I collect symbols used within this notebook. ", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"c3db4546-64de-4d22-85ae-bc0d3567ac4b"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["How to use this notebook", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"17668f86-1928-4c4f-8889-49f1042ab36c"],

Cell["\<\
Simply evaluate the \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Load Dump File\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] section. It is important that both the current \
notebook
and the provided storage file are located at the same folder.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"4bca8eb6-d2eb-45a6-ac9f-dce2a22f4d26"]
}, Closed]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Color", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"6b92e068-2238-4a6f-9785-46ef51fa8348"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Color factors ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"(", 
    SubscriptBox["N", "c"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "028ccad1-23ef-4c89-bcec-8a35e24d9ba7"],
 "\[Equivalent]NC=3)"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"143be534-fc7d-45a1-83ed-765d368a8533"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"cF", "\[Rule]", 
    FractionBox[
     RowBox[{
      SuperscriptBox["NC", "2"], "-", "1"}], 
     RowBox[{"2", "NC"}]]}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"cA", "\[Rule]", "NC"}], ",", " ", 
   RowBox[{"tR", "\[Rule]", 
    RowBox[{"1", "/", "2"}]}]}], "}"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[1]:=",ExpressionUUID->"9ef36154-46ca-439c-ae6f-90bce774575d"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"cF", "\[Rule]", 
    FractionBox[
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"-", "1"}], "+", 
      SuperscriptBox["NC", "2"]}], 
     RowBox[{"2", " ", "NC"}]]}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"cA", "\[Rule]", "NC"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"tR", "\[Rule]", 
    FractionBox["1", "2"]}]}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->"Out[1]=",ExpressionUUID->"384dab64-8dc7-4073-97dd-f36af19c2f20"]
}, Closed]],

Cell["\<\
tR is everywhere replaced by its value in the coefficients and here only for \
reference.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"4cf9b6f6-3dcd-46fd-a840-81158441fbac"]
}, Closed]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["GPLs", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"f8c2b3e0-b0bf-48d4-89cd-fcd2d626daca"],

Cell["\<\
We use the notation of Gonacharov polylogarithms (GPLs) compatible with GiNaC \
which can be accessed 
through PolyLogTools interface. \
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"e1f55d04-e6bd-4f96-a143-1ea498d477c5"],

Cell["\<\
However, for the bookkeeping purpose, we keep the iterated integrals, briefly \
mentioned in the paper. \[LineSeparator]They are mapped to the GPLs via \
``mapIteratedIntegrals\[CloseCurlyQuote]\[CloseCurlyQuote]\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"7d6261ed-2bbb-4106-a7e2-2c11f663ddcd"]
}, Closed]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Other", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"8d18d157-7704-4e31-8c85-e2be31bb5897"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The definition of the variables is defined in the paper.\n\
\[LineSeparator]",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"y1", "->", 
     SubscriptBox["y", "1"]}], ",", 
    RowBox[{"y2", "->", 
     SubscriptBox["y", "2"]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "5cd2db81-e6cd-4b30-a7dd-39dc9f2a68d5"],
 "\n\nThey can be mapped to the \[Xi]\[CloseCurlyQuote](\[Xi]pr) defined in \
Ref.~[1].\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"{", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"y1", "\[Rule]", 
     RowBox[{"1", "-", "\[Xi]pr"}]}], ",", 
    RowBox[{"y2", "\[Rule]", 
     RowBox[{"m2", " ", 
      FractionBox["\[Xi]pr", 
       RowBox[{"Q2", "+", 
        RowBox[{"m2", " ", "\[Xi]pr"}]}]]}]}]}], "}"}]], "Input",
  ExpressionUUID->"61644dbb-7543-40ce-8cf5-4cafc604ed37"],
 "\n\n\[Xi]pr is related to the \[Xi]-scaling variable from Ref[1] in our \
case via\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"{", 
   RowBox[{"\[Xi]pr", "\[Rule]", 
    FractionBox["x", "\[Xi]"]}], "}"}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID->
  "1a1a9b38-b4c5-481d-9e75-a2c44b089e94"],
 ",\n\nwhere x is Bjorken-x. \nNOTE: we drop \[OpenCurlyQuote]pr\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] bit and use plane \[Xi] instead in our calculations \
but this is not the ACOT\[CloseCurlyQuote]s \[Xi].\n\nHere, m2 - the \
heavy-quark squared mass, Q2 -  the squared virtuality of the boson, s = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox[
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"q", "+", "p"}], ")"}], "2"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "f63de376-41a5-4804-9c57-3e759371844b"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SqrtBox["s"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "a0b9fa17-3566-4760-9a94-ff10d04bf500"],
 "- the partonic center-of-mass energy.\n\n- TAG[wmq1] \[Rule] the \
heavy-quark initiated DIS;\n- TAG[wmpq1] \[Rule] the heavy-antiquark \
initiated DIS.\n\nTHETA is the Heaviside function that designate a particle \
production thresholds: single heavy particle (s - m^2) and heavy pair (s - \
4m^2).\n\nVCKM[CS] -> the CKM matrix element V_{cs}.\nVCKM[UD] -> the CKM \
matrix element V_{ud}.\nSINGLET is a tag that indicates the contribution from \
sea-like diagrams with a closed box fermion loop.\n\nIn case of VCKM[CS], the \
diagrams includes two flavors: heavy and light; VCKM[UD] correspond to one \
flavor only in the fermion loop.\[LineSeparator]Thus, it is  up to the user \
how to sum over the flavors at this point. The substitution below correctly \
reproduce\[LineSeparator]the MSbar result in the m^2/Q^2 \[Rule] 0 limit\n\n\
VCKM[UD]^2 * SINGLET -> VCKM[UD]^2 * (nL+nH)/2,\n\nUsing these rules, we \
correctly reproduce the pure-singlet contribution ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubsuperscriptBox["T", 
    RowBox[{"i", ",", " ", "q"}], 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"(", "2", ")"}], ",", " ", "ps"}]], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"7b391876-6256-4c37-82e3-124643224561"],
 " from Ref.~[3], in the m/Q\[Rule]0 limit. \n\nThe plus distributions read \
in our case\nPD[a_] = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     RowBox[{"[", 
      FractionBox[
       SuperscriptBox[
        RowBox[{"Log", "[", 
         SubscriptBox["y", "1"], "]"}], 
        RowBox[{"a", "-", "1"}]], 
       SubscriptBox["y", "1"]], "]"}], "+"], ",", " ", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"for", " ", "a"}], "=", "1"}], ",", "2", ",", "..."}], 
   TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->"599ec9a9-9079-4388-9546-8951d90833d5"],
 "; ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"PD", "[", "0", "]"}], "=", 
    RowBox[{"\[Delta]", "(", 
     SubscriptBox["y", "1"]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "ad084284-4cf0-47ee-b1d8-f9048985c9c1"],
 ").\nor if \[Xi] is used\n\nPD[a_] = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     RowBox[{"[", 
      FractionBox[
       SuperscriptBox[
        RowBox[{"Log", "[", 
         RowBox[{"1", "-", "\[Xi]"}], "]"}], 
        RowBox[{"a", "-", "1"}]], 
       RowBox[{"1", "-", "\[Xi]"}]], "]"}], "+"], ",", " ", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"for", " ", "a"}], "=", "1"}], ",", "2", ",", "..."}], 
   TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->"e59e0865-c275-4e7a-9522-1b2e19fd470c"],
 "; ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"PD", "[", "0", "]"}], "=", 
    RowBox[{"\[Delta]", "(", 
     RowBox[{"1", "-", "\[Xi]"}]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "5f836805-cebf-4c29-b354-bf0e3468cc0a"],
 ").\n\nCitations:\n[1] - Kretzer, S. and Schienbein, I. \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Heavy quark initiated contributions to deep inelastic \
structure functions\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote];\n[2] - ACOT, \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Leptoproduction of heavy quarks. 1. General formalism \
and kinematics of charged current and neutral current production processes\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote];\n[3] - S. Moch, J.A.M. Vermaseren, \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Deep-inelastic structure functions at two loops\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"a8b79342-8b6d-4d22-9f8a-f01549fe13f1"]
}, Closed]]
}, Closed]]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Coefficient Functions", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"a393e728-3ca1-4ced-9fdb-0b1e5c6350fa"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"Quit", "[", "]"}], ";"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[3]:=",ExpressionUUID->"7e21ef20-5f48-4a1f-b6aa-bfdd213d21ed"],

